Reasoning: The paper focuses on the analysis and modification of 3D structures in additive manufacturing, which involves computational geometry (cs.CG) and computer graphics (cs.GR) techniques. The use of machine learning (cs.MS) and computer vision (cs.CV) is also possible for analyzing and detecting defects in the as-manufactured structures. Additionally, the paper mentions the limitations of available 3D printer resolution, which falls under the scope of multimedia (cs.MM).
